 TWO persons died on Monday while six others sustained serious injuries in a multiple road crash involving five vehicles in Anambra State. The incident took place at Mike Ajegbo Road in Obosi, Idemili South Local Government Area of the state. Twenty-one persons were involved in the crash, it was gathered. The Nation learned that a truck driver lost control and crashed into other vehicles. The truck exploded into flames. Sector Public Education Officer, Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC), Pascal Anigbo, confirmed the crash, attributing it to speeding.